{"sectionId":785,"sectionIdLiteral":"785","humanId":"lesson-360","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"Peace be to me, the holy Son of God.  Peace to my brother, who is one with me.  Let all the world be blessed with peace through us.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 360"},"annotation":"W-360","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-360\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"785#1\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"785#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, it is Your peace that I would give, receiving it of You.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"785#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I am Your Son, forever just as You created me, for the Great Rays remain forever still and undisturbed within me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"785#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>I would reach to them in silence and in certainty, for nowhere else can certainty be found.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"785#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Peace be to me, and peace to all the world.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"785#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>In holiness were we created, and in holiness do we remain.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"785#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>Your Son is like to You in perfect sinlessness.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"785#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>And with this thought we gladly say ‚ÄúAmen.‚Äù</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Father, it is Your peace that I would give, receiving it of You. I am Your Son, forever just as You created me, for the Great Rays remain forever still and undisturbed within me. I would reach to","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 360: Peace be to me, the holy Son of‚Ä¶ | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†360 ‚ÄúPeace be to me, the holy Son of God. Peace to my brother, who is one with me. Let all the world be blessed with peace through us‚Äù: ‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Wo